==English==
===Etymology===
The [[life jacket]] was named after the [[actress]] and [[sex symbol]] [[w:Mae West|Mae West]], who was well known during the war, the inflatable front taken to be like her [[bust]]y figure.
===Proper noun===
'''Mae West'''
# American [[actress]], [[playwright]] and [[sex symbol]] (born 1892 or 93, died 1980).
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# Nickname for a type of [[life jacket]] used by Allied forces in [[World War II]] having an inflatable rubber bag on the chest of the wearer.
